result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota Evan Ranney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dakota Evan Ranney is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dakota Evan Ranney was found guilty of Attempt Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

THE COURT FINDS:
1.  The inmate has not previously petitioned for sentence adjustment under 973.195, Wis. Stats.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Dakota Evan Ranney in court with attorney Haley Breese Wright.  Defendant Dakota Evan Ranney in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Court advises defendant of elements of count 3 & max. penalties and advises defendant of his constitutional rights.  Defendant pleads "no contest".  PLQ/WRF filed with the court & reviewed with defendant.  Court finds defendant's waiver of his const. rts. & plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty.  All other counts dismissed.  No PSI requested.  Revocation packet was provided to DA in lieu of PSI.  Court sentenced defendant to 5 yrs. in WI State Prison, 18 mos. initial confinement followed by 3 1/2 yrs. of E.S.  Court waives costs on this case, orders defendant to provide a DNA sample unless already one one.  Sentence concurrent to Dunn Co. Case #10CF200 and anticipated concurrent to Buffalo Co. Case No. 10CF83 & 84 when sentence pronounced.  Court finds defendant eligible for SAP & CIP.  Appeal rights given.

Defendant Dakota Evan Ranney in court with attorney Haley Breese Wright.  Defendant Dakota Evan Ranney in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Counsel informs the court of resolution with joint recommendation.  Defendant waives right to P.H., waiver form filed with the court.
